#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:5
msgid "Marking test functions with attributes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:9
msgid ""
"By using the ``pytest.mark`` helper you can easily set metadata on your test "
"functions. There are some builtin markers, for example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:13
msgid ""
":ref:`skipif <skipif>` - skip a test function if a certain condition is met"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:14
msgid ""
":ref:`xfail <xfail>` - produce an \"expected failure\" outcome if a certain "
"condition is met"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:16
msgid ""
":ref:`parametrize <parametrizemark>` to perform multiple calls to the same "
"test function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:19
msgid ""
"It's easy to create custom markers or to apply markers to whole test classes "
"or modules. See :ref:`mark examples` for examples which also serve as "
"documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:25
msgid ""
"Marks can only be applied to tests, having no effect on :ref:`fixtures "
"<fixtures>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/mark.rst:30
msgid "API reference for mark related objects"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/mark.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.mark.MarkGenerator:1
msgid ""
"Factory for :class:`MarkDecorator` objects - exposed as a ``pytest.mark`` "
"singleton instance.  Example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/mark.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.mark.MarkGenerator:4
msgid ""
"import pytest\n"
"@pytest.mark.slowtest\n"
"def test_function():\n"
"   pass"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/mark.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.mark.MarkGenerator:9
msgid ""
"will set a 'slowtest' :class:`MarkInfo` object on the ``test_function`` "
"object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/mark.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.mark.MarkDecorator:1
msgid ""
"A decorator for test functions and test classes.  When applied it will "
"create :class:`MarkInfo` objects which may be :ref:`retrieved by hooks as "
"item keywords <excontrolskip>`. MarkDecorator instances are often created "
"like this::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/mark.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.mark.MarkDecorator:6
msgid ""
"mark1 = pytest.mark.NAME              # simple MarkDecorator\n"
"mark2 = pytest.mark.NAME(name1=value) # parametrized MarkDecorator"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/mark.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.mark.MarkDecorator:9
msgid "and can then be applied as decorators to test functions::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/mark.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.mark.MarkDecorator:11
msgid ""
"@mark2\n"
"def test_function():\n"
"    pass"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/mark.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.mark.MarkDecorator:26
msgid "When a MarkDecorator instance is called it does the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/mark.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.mark.MarkDecorator:16
msgid ""
"If called with a single class as its only positional argument and no "
"additional keyword arguments, it attaches itself to the class so it gets "
"applied automatically to all test cases found in that class."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/mark.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.mark.MarkDecorator:19
msgid ""
"If called with a single function as its only positional argument and no "
"additional keyword arguments, it attaches a MarkInfo object to the function, "
"containing all the arguments already stored internally in the MarkDecorator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/mark.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.mark.MarkDecorator:23
msgid ""
"When called in any other case, it performs a 'fake construction' call, i.e. "
"it returns a new MarkDecorator instance with the original MarkDecorator's "
"content updated with the arguments passed to this call."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/mark.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.mark.MarkDecorator:28
msgid ""
"Note: The rules above prevent MarkDecorator objects from storing only a "
"single function or class reference as their positional argument with no "
"additional keyword or positional arguments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/mark.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.mark.MarkInfo:1
msgid "Marking object created by :class:`MarkDecorator` instances."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/docstring of _pytest.mark.MarkInfo.name:1
msgid "name of attribute"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/docstring of _pytest.mark.MarkInfo.args:1
msgid "positional argument list, empty if none specified"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/docstring of _pytest.mark.MarkInfo.kwargs:1
msgid "keyword argument dictionary, empty if nothing specified"
msgstr ""

